3msKSD_AFrChP33a4cu8X06IBwLhQep5zn815oxUliAB8rc0GDtGMlgafe_mNVQQQwBMFpMuBpNQ13ls29kZSZWgESNM8d-voP9xETFUhKbVWmhEFgTqKi76jDvLWGkP8JYD9tiixxCaMatIvL7A69CBX4MpbXmwJzqCN0V5GU4ZNz_8QUx7GPfoIokVjF9OmfKHulkAav2jmA8SsGMhszGerNCVcN4ILQtmnNOOSsqv0IQfl6gjCH2Peiu1Bf8GSU0i0nqZjOvlJIURwex0d7g44ZVPM5Azx-WKd_BLUuLPoSQd3JO5M2POyRCd5bGOb9q-K\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring test behavior**\\n\\nI'm considering how to make a test pass natively using `@Test` while catching a `MockitoException`, but only if the error message is non-specific. It seems like the behavior differs between JVM and native images. The contract says they should behave the same, but I’m unsure. \\n\\nWhat if I assert that the inline mock maker can report mockability or force the same behavior on both platforms? I’m also thinking about spawning a new Java process to handle classpath issues, but that might complicate things!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering class loading options**\\n\\nI'm thinking about whether I could create a custom ClassLoader to isolate and load `InlineDelegateByteBuddyMockMaker` after setting a property. However, direct class loading or reflection seems prohibited. Can I cover static initialization resources by using a manual `Mockito.mock(... INLINE)`? If it fails after metadata, that's a concern. The deliverable will likely be assessed based on Java coverage, and the developer’s standards are quite strict. I wonder if I could still catch errors in a sanctioned way, but that doesn’t seem likely.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_Q04lAjHMFQGmAjVfL9p7lMF5|fc_06ec292419a8e6ab016a2abb9396c48197ac98549e1b6cccfc", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.mockito/mockito-core/5.0.0/src/test/java/org_mockito/mockito_core/InlineDelegateByteBuddyMockMakerTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_mockito.mockito_core;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\nimport static org.mockito.ArgumentMatchers.anyInt;\nimport static org.mockito.ArgumentMatchers.anyString;\nimport static org.mockito.ArgumentMatchers.eq;\nimport static org.mockito.Mockito.mock;\nimport static org.mockito.Mockito.verify;\nimport static org.mockito.Mockito.when;\nimport static org.mockito.Mockito.withSettings;\n\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\nimport org.mockito.ArgumentCaptor;\nimport org.mockito.Mock;\nimport org.mockito.MockMakers;\nimport org.mockito.Mockito;\nimport org.mockito.MockitoSession;\nimport org.mockito.quality.Strictness;\n\npublic class InlineDelegateByteBuddyMockMakerTest {\n    @Mock(mockMaker = MockMakers.INLINE)\n    InlineOrderService annotatedService;\n\n    @Test\n    void createsConcreteMockWithInlineMockMakerAndCustomAnswer() {\n        InlineOrderService service =\n                mock(InlineOrderService.class, withSettings().mockMaker(MockMakers.INLINE));\n\n        when(service.price(anyString(), anyInt()))\n                .thenAnswer(\n                        invocation -> {\n                            String sku = invocation.getArgument(0);\n                            int quantity = invocation.getArgument(1);\n                            return \"premium\".equals(sku) ? quantity * 25 : quantity * 10;\n                        });\n\n        assertThat(service.price(\"premium\", 3)).isEqualTo(75);\n        assertThat(service.price(\"standard\", 4)).isEqualTo(40);\n\n        ArgumentCaptor<String> skuCaptor = ArgumentCaptor.forClass(String.class);\n        verify(service).price(skuCaptor.capture(), eq(3));\n        assertThat(skuCaptor.getValue()).isEqualTo(\"premium\");\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void initializesAnnotatedConcreteInlineMockInMockitoSession() {\n        MockitoSession session =\n                Mockito.mockitoSession()\n                        .initMocks(this)\n                        .strictness(Strictness.STRICT_STUBS)\n                        .startMocking();\n        try {\n            when(annotatedService.describe(\"standard\")).thenReturn(\"mocked standard order\");\n\n            assertThat(annotatedService.describe(\"standard\")).isEqualTo(\"mocked standard order\");\n            verify(annotatedService).describe(\"standard\");\n        } finally {\n            session.finishMocking();\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static class InlineOrderService {\n        private final String source;\n        private final int basePrice;\n\n        public InlineOrderService(String source, int basePrice) {\n            this.source = source == null ? \"default\" : source;\n            this.basePrice = basePrice;\n        }\n\n        public int price(String sku, int quantity) {\n            return basePrice + sku.length() + quantity;\n        }\n\n        public String describe(String sku) {\n            return source + \" \" + sku;\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 27712, "output": 2416, "cacheRead": 11264, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 41392, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1781185387109, "responseId": "resp_06ec292419a8e6ab016a2abb6bb1b88197aaeca0f8b42005f0"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_Q04lAjHMFQGmAjVfL9p7lMF5|fc_06ec292419a8e6ab016a2abb9396c48197ac98549e1b6cccfc", "toolName": "write", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully wrote 3063 bytes to tests/src/org.mockito/mockito-core/5.0.0/src/test/java/org_mockito/mockito_core/InlineDelegateByteBuddyMockMakerTest.java"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1781185436339}]}
