[thinking] I'm looking into the issue that arises when loading the default plugin with Mockito. It turns out that the default behavior in mockito-core 5.0 is to use inline mocking, unless a resource subclass overrides it. If that's the case, the default plugin may not use inline.
[thinking] 
[thinking] Now, the per-mock mockMaker tries to instantiate InlineByteBuddyMockMaker, which triggers a specific constructor line. This line, 230, only invokes the ToolProvider reflectively if there's an INIT_ERROR. But wait, our JVM has actually succeeded in its initialization, so I wonder if there's an error path associated with line 230 that we need to explore further. I’ll map it out more precisely.
[thinking] 
[assistant-event] thinking_end
