[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Addressing Java compatibility issues**\n\nI’m facing a challenge with running tests due to ByteBuddy being unsupported on Java 25. The error suggests setting the net.bytebuddy.experimental VM property to enable support, which seems common for older versions on newer Java. The developer advises against asserting a version-specific failure, but maybe updating the build.gradle file is necessary if new tests require this.\n\nWhile existing tests passed with a concrete subclass, inline retransform is failing. I need to be careful with native images, as they don’t support inline mocking. This could lead to issues with future inline tests.\n\n**Evaluating native test compatibility**\n\nI need to ensure that the tests behave similarly in both the JVM and native environments. It seems that the active class call sites might only work with a JVM agent, which could lead to failures in native. The rules are strict about not skipping anything, but perhaps the native image test compiles, and the inline mock maker initialization just can’t happen at runtime.\n\nCurrent tests have failed with the native plugin, but maybe generated metadata and subclass extensions could still pass. If the native fails later, it reflects poorly on inline tests, yet we need to cover call sites since they rely on the inline mock maker. There are recommendations against using proxy-only overrides, suggesting I should focus on covering non-final concrete classes and avoid only inline features.\n\n**Analyzing Mockito plugin behavior**\n\nI'm looking into the issue that arises when loading the default plugin with Mockito. It turns out that the default behavior in mockito-core 5.0 is to use inline mocking, unless a resource subclass overrides it. If that's the case, the default plugin may not use inline.\n\nNow, the per-mock mockMaker tries to instantiate InlineByteBuddyMockMaker, which triggers a specific constructor line. This line, 230, only invokes the ToolProvider reflectively if there's an INIT_ERROR. But wait, our JVM has actually succeeded in its initialization, so I wonder if there's an error path associated with line 230 that we need to explore further. I’ll map it out more precisely.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_06ec292419a8e6ab016a2abbda5cfc8197ac0799f72aa728b0\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqKrv_COUo6UKLKiXUnXm6VcZ5K1uyZrbaV_4Ld_ZlSxdo3ds-OCf6MxsU51_tVkke7Rs6LwE-skPRuSdlJPT2Pw7QqPskQJtWfTGqUezDGrhHNJmaoZ5KBIEcfXw9iLKPWLy9Og0YjnRzUG7OCfWFdD09lmJ7LhBfBTdg7ocW_wdqtCJl1fCry-4pAEdDWmglWxGNpVweE_xVF6j1_-xjnUqDZgL_Gmbr4MBdayvFh28Y5Z09cvaRV13IRIGyAOMRKhem-0czxiWlCODqGOGJwv08FKxlShk75EMfsHUYnOnzjaSImJWN_UsHyIeFCk_Nt6V0-7NQ2vw0pJoTqkcdOsrFVXJQ5Rc2wIMZhvqpbgTRAEKSAmRIhth1wSRCiMVWXtxFfa3gHLUB__qt5P1vtkylyVyvOhogPGAQfnjCM5bc2VUWloPgydPg_b-u6fbdirUQJwf7Ri0X0zYZx62TysFrntYlKuYkh4BGLi7qFWMRsAHccdceArOKEdmEDoK_DA0CeyT-OTRqrin0X6JEJDsO5U7aePeX7o3un2Egy7GALsQzxWcAxVF_sLOVdTWaPB9xDXT2njgyjsc9uwpozGFy0NLOeOTGFoa7ED14nSS5ylEpfFbvzDTsP67BAS6cOpa_-fxFrqrOwwdWLgyIsW5ieiWquNXcM2g8ojx9tIqF0ItcfeZ2KLQC9lnOjNGiR9McqUz50FrK7ThGkews1oCUBjwPp3Lp-iq0CJufb4bBA6qf7z_ZMKFdi1J3t3Mirrud9Fdp42ecCiG9l9FUpSBAa7qptLyJW9a3SMuiymwvJbwDhTtPVkn_HFSOEzGTaDe7XJSbzXah03UQOOdglHohwMyGUIZQzBP95ClOdIk-Pt7bakfclkXwQSaox3Rd5oqSdnoVYqvLk5-ghUlJbmPcBlR4ETUf5ciEKBGJf9SNvo8_xzgIYs_Fyjk0hr2hxgddN46F_pgiazjQk3wvSi78Xm2UYZEMll6d_TgIzh5TRFRG08g09VwSgviQp9UhgpaUi6Zo5mDzGwbBxltJBgRsbp22G2SmeCl8b6kzokZaoz7l6Eb1WXlQ9OAPNdAsGkJxPHKRMfvyX8QEgyeP8660XbGK-b6Rrl3kKKpvEhPbbi6gc_NG_cVUokMqGYB9SuQiM6kjTYpeLPUEpzZL8vv0E51TDPWOb4_uuk2vbGBleCNQ7mM0cagmjnPPzBBPJPwz-i1PcdtlIKUT7jaLVmKdU6L_6B2ILOWuYmKH8Uc0cmY539F7-4fiisulmpt1ENDDhSZ-_7wPsZkABiwdsvQA9gpz2cI2kr9tJfphQFUoTTuUiimvSf18h00IPuRydVbVVLB1yv_MsKMzyIrEg4CFN70GdcN8eVnYsMwEc9hm4wBBSWYJvzWspDOXFmibynpVqYNyaL_JuUmCDJlNNr3P7gZZEh9Bx1w4NHSBAPShNDNFNGlKVfW1vf__D00h3szHgwOU_rclw7YMp1CTIoYBn588JFTU8p6Kdrf6pleuqfxosN7Q7mXfIbzExN5JK_y3