ype\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing Mockito plugin behavior**\\n\\nI'm looking into the issue that arises when loading the default plugin with Mockito. It turns out that the default behavior in mockito-core 5.0 is to use inline mocking, unless a resource subclass overrides it. If that's the case, the default plugin may not use inline.\\n\\nNow, the per-mock mockMaker tries to instantiate InlineByteBuddyMockMaker, which triggers a specific constructor line. This line, 230, only invokes the ToolProvider reflectively if there's an INIT_ERROR. But wait, our JVM has actually succeeded in its initialization, so I wonder if there's an error path associated with line 230 that we need to explore further. I’ll map it out more precisely.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_Du4g2OP4lN5ixG6RxkRVbPfI|fc_06ec292419a8e6ab016a2abbff2da48197ae1ea31e0bb5aed4", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg \"NativeImageSupport|isUnsupportedFeatureError|mockMaker\\(MockMakers.INLINE|net.bytebuddy.experimental\" tests/src/org.mockito -n | head -100"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 28891, "output": 1471, "cacheRead": 12800, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 43162, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1781185495948, "responseId": "resp_06ec292419a8e6ab016a2abbd986a081978dc8cc7588e2e9b6"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_Du4g2OP4lN5ixG6RxkRVbPfI|fc_06ec292419a8e6ab016a2abbff2da48197ae1ea31e0bb5aed4", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "tests/src/org.mockito/mockito-core/5.0.0/src/test/java/org_mockito/mockito_core/InlineDelegateByteBuddyMockMakerTest.java:33:                mock(InlineOrderService.class, withSettings().mockMaker(MockMakers.INLINE));\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1781185535815}]}
