[assistant] Fixed the classloader issue causing `ClassCastException`.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Root cause: the isolated `URLClassLoader` loaded Mockito classes, but Mockito’s `MockUtil` uses the thread context classloader to load the selected `MockMaker`. The context classloader was still the system Gradle/JUnit loader, so `InlineByteBuddyMockMaker` and `MockMaker` came from different classloaders.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Change made in:
[assistant] 
[assistant] - `tests/src/org.mockito/mockito-core/5.0.0/src/test/java/org_mockito/mockito_core/InlineDelegateByteBuddyMockMakerTest.java`
[assistant] 
[assistant] Updates:
[assistant] - Set the thread context classloader to the isolated child classloader while invoking the isolated Mockito scenario.
[assistant] - Restore the original context classloader in `finally`.
[assistant] - Adjusted the initialization-diagnostic assertion to match Mockito’s actual public failure shape: `IllegalStateException("Failed to construct MockMaker...")` with a Mockito initialization exception in its cause chain.
[assistant] 
[assistant] No tests were run locally.
