aVPSXQzJW1eI2Q5CEk7uD5B12xEi538KIJ6-OA_qZsgMmSdHPgd7nV6uAVDs1CtU1atkDaeAHQub3-_ekE4LIKPGidPrXUNlIptSDkDGkKiOP15LaJ7S4LROt5Q69Xn-36WRfOVc3NDsErHsIY4O0WXxg==\",\"summary\":[]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Fixed the classloader issue causing `ClassCastException`.\n\nRoot cause: the isolated `URLClassLoader` loaded Mockito classes, but Mockito’s `MockUtil` uses the thread context classloader to load the selected `MockMaker`. The context classloader was still the system Gradle/JUnit loader, so `InlineByteBuddyMockMaker` and `MockMaker` came from different classloaders.\n\nChange made in:\n\n- `tests/src/org.mockito/mockito-core/5.0.0/src/test/java/org_mockito/mockito_core/InlineDelegateByteBuddyMockMakerTest.java`\n\nUpdates:\n- Set the thread context classloader to the isolated child classloader while invoking the isolated Mockito scenario.\n- Restore the original context classloader in `finally`.\n- Adjusted the initialization-diagnostic assertion to match Mockito’s actual public failure shape: `IllegalStateException(\"Failed to construct MockMaker...\")` with a Mockito initialization exception in its cause chain.\n\nNo tests were run locally.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_06ec292419a8e6ab016a2abeff85188197b39997db9261b452\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1257, "output": 1349, "cacheRead": 73728, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 76334, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1781186276813, "responseId": "resp_06ec292419a8e6ab016a2abee5b4bc8197854dd3c6f2da8758"}}
